# Dreamr Coding Conventions

## Imports
- Use `@/` path alias for all internal imports (maps to `src/`)
- Group imports: 1) external packages, 2) `@/lib/`, 3) `@/components/`, 4) `@/hooks/`, 5) relative
- Separate groups with blank lines

## File Ownership (Multi-Agent)
- **Agent A (Backend)**: `src/app/api/**`, `src/lib/fal/**`, `src/lib/marble/**`, `src/lib/inngest/functions/**`, `src/lib/supabase/server.ts`, `src/lib/supabase/admin.ts`, `src/proxy.ts`, `supabase/**`
- **Agent B (Frontend)**: `src/components/**`, `src/hooks/**`, `src/lib/stores/**`, `src/app/(pages)/**`, `src/app/layout.tsx`, `src/styles/**`, `src/lib/supabase/client.ts`
- **Shared (Foundation only)**: `src/lib/types/**`, `src/lib/supabase/types.ts`, `src/lib/inngest/client.ts`, `src/lib/utils/**`, `src/test/fixtures/**`
- Do NOT edit files outside your ownership unless coordinating a contract change

## React Components
- Always add `"use client"` for components using hooks, state, or browser APIs
- Use named exports, not default exports, for components
- Props interfaces should be defined in the same file, named `{ComponentName}Props`
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils/cn` for conditional class names

## Supabase
- Always check `.error` on Supabase responses before using `.data`
- Use `createServerSupabase()` in API routes (respects RLS via cookies)
- Use `createAdminSupabase()` in Inngest functions (bypasses RLS)
- Use `createBrowserSupabase()` in client components
- Never use the service role key on the client

## Inngest
- Each pipeline step should be a separate `step.run()` call
- Never use long-running `while` loops inside `step.run()` — use `step.sleep()` between polling attempts
- Always update `pipeline_jobs` table status for real-time UI updates
- Use typed event schemas from `@/lib/inngest/client`

## API Routes
- Always verify auth with `await auth()` from `@clerk/nextjs/server`
- Return proper HTTP status codes (401 unauthorized, 404 not found, 400 bad request)
- Use `NextResponse.json()` for all responses
- Verify resource ownership before mutations
- Dynamic route params use `params: Promise<{ paramName: string }>` in Next.js 15+

## Error Handling
- API routes: catch errors, return JSON `{ error: string }` with appropriate status
- Inngest functions: let errors bubble for automatic retries, log context
- Client components: use React Error Boundaries around R3F Canvas
- Always provide user-facing error messages (not raw stack traces)

## Styling
- Use Tailwind utility classes with CSS custom properties from globals.css
- Use `.glow-border`, `.glow-button`, `.glow-animated` for themed interactive elements
- Dark theme only — all colors reference CSS variables
- Use Framer Motion for transitions and animations

## Testing
- Test files live next to source files as `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx`
- Use mock fixtures from `@/test/fixtures` for consistent test data
- Mock external APIs (fal.ai, Marble, Supabase) — never call real APIs in tests
- Test Zustand stores by calling actions and asserting state
